    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "MEASUREMENTS "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                84,
                66,
                227,
                80
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Signal processing unit for DRXLs consists of sensing parts (charge amplifier, high pass filter, amplifier) and driving parts (phase shifter, rectifier, comparator, amplifier) as shown in Fig. 4. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                81,
                85,
                482,
                147
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/04bea005d32a23f4892e0e4681f0c307b5f66e55a30f2e6e4916f8801954541e.jpg"
                },
                "image_caption": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Fig. 4. Signal-processing unit for DRXL "
                    }
                ],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                83,
                162,
                488,
                368
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "In sensing parts, the minute signal from the accelerometer is detected and amplified by charge amplifier, the unwanted signal such as  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "60\\mathrm{Hz}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " noise is rejected in high pass filter and output signal is generated by amplifying the resultant signal. For driving resonator of DRXL, the output signal in sensing parts is used to generate driving signal. The phase shifter and rectifier are adopted for self-oscillation and dc voltage respectively, the comparator is used to make square-wave signal and the amplifier is used to adjust the amplitude of driving signal. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                81,
                409,
                482,
                556
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The fabricated accelerometer is tested by applying the gravitational force of  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "-1\\mathrm{g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ",  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0\\mathrm{g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ",  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1\\mathrm{g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". One resonator shows sensitivity of  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "64\\mathrm{Hz / g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " at nominal frequency of  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "23.4\\mathrm{kHz}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " and the other resonator shows sensitivity of  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "64\\mathrm{Hz / g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " at nominal frequency of  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "33.4\\mathrm{kHz}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " as shown in Fig. 5. Therefore, the differential output between two resonators shows  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "128\\mathrm{Hz / g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". The mechanical quality factor is about 200. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                81,
                579,
                482,
                696
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/7514dffbd9116e62e2f2126adf62c6e0f79fadcae64502e8a4c2f8262c89f53f.jpg"
                },
                "image_caption": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Fig. 5. Tumble test result "
                    }
                ],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                86,
                718,
                434,
                896
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The output frequency fluctuation is important factor to determine the resolution of DRXL, so the Allan variance is measured using SR(Stanford Research)620 frequency counter. The measured result is shown in Fig. 6. The resonant frequency is measured at a different sampling time; 0.01 sec, 0.1 sec, 1 sec, 10 sec. At each sampling time, the frequency is measured 5 times repetitively and averaged. As the sampling time larger, the Allan variance converges a certain value as shown in Fig. 6. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                511,
                104,
                913,
                238
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/f259dcb1f47a08c9b5926d318dd8698e387ee3bb59a634fc3756ff904a15fe0e.jpg"
                },
                "image_caption": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Fig. 6. Measured Allan variance "
                    }
                ],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                526,
                268,
                895,
                477
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The bandwidth of DRXL is also important parameter, so it is measured by applying a step function electrically to proof mass of the accelerometer. The measured output signal for fabricated accelerometer is shown in Fig. 7. The estimated bandwidth is about  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "110\\mathrm{Hz}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                511,
                517,
                911,
                590
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
